definition.value: Any substance that interacts with tubulin to inhibit or promote polymerisation of microtubules.
A dicarboxylic acid monoamide which results from addition of one equivalent of 1-naphthylamine to phthalic anhydride.
Any pyridoindole containing a beta-carboline skeleton and their hydrogenated derivatives

A hydroxyflavan with hydroxy groups at positions 3 and 4. Further oxygenation may be present at other ring positions. They are considered as derivatives of anthocyanidin and hence are termed leucoanthocyanidin.
A family of peptides related to glutathione and composed of (gamma-Glu-Cys)n-Gly where n is in the range 2-11.
A 2',3'-cyclic nucleotide(1-) which is obtained from 2',3'-cyclic GMP by removal of a proton from the cyclic phosphate group.
A primary aliphatic ammonium ion which is obtained from streptothricin F by protonation of the guanidino and amino groups and deprotonation of the carboxylic acid group.
A primary aliphatic ammonium ion which is obtained from streptothricin D by protonation of the guanidino and amino groups and deprotonation of the carboxylic acid group.
A 2,3-dihydro-3-hydroxyanthranilic acid in which the stereocentre attached to the amino group has R-configuration, whilst that attached to the hydroxy group has S-configuration.
An amino alcohol which is 2,3-dihydranthranilic acid in which a hydrogen at position 3 is substituted by a hydroxy group.
A 2,3-dihydro-3-hydroxyanthranilic acid in which the stereocentre attached to the amino group has S-configuration, whilst that attached to the hydroxy group has R-configuration.
A 2,3-dihydro-3-hydroxyanthranilic acid in which both stereocentres have R-configuration.
A 2,3-dihydro-3-hydroxyanthranilic acid in which both stereocentres have S-configuration.
A 2,3-dihydro-3-hydroxyanthranilic acid zwitterion, obtained by transfer of a proton from the carboxylic acid group to the amino group of (2R,3S)-2,3-dihydro-3-hydroxyanthranilic acid.
A 2,3-dihydro-3-hydroxyanthranilic acid zwitterion, obtained by transfer of a proton from the carboxylic acid group to the amino group of (2S,3R)-2,3-dihydro-3-hydroxyanthranilic acid.
An amino acid zwitterion, obtained by transfer of a proton from the carboxylic acid group to the amino group of 2,3-dihydro-3-hydroxyanthranilic acid.
A 2,3-dihydro-3-hydroxyanthranilic acid zwitterion, obtained by transfer of a proton from the carboxylic acid group to the amino group of (2R,3R)-2,3-dihydro-3-hydroxyanthranilic acid.
A 2,3-dihydro-3-hydroxyanthranilic acid zwitterion, obtained by transfer of a proton from the carboxylic acid group to the amino group of (2S,3S)-2,3-dihydro-3-hydroxyanthranilic acid.
A racemate comprising (2R,3S)- and (2S,3R)-2,3-dihydro-3-hydroxyanthranilic acid.
A racemate comprising (2R,3R)- and (2S,3S)-2,3-dihydro-3-hydroxyanthranilic acid.
A 2,3-dihydro-3-hydroxyanthranilic acid zwitterion racemate comprising (2R,3S)- and (2S,3R)-2,3-dihydro-3-hydroxyanthranilic acid zwitterion.
A 2,3-dihydro-3-hydroxyanthranilic acid zwitterion racemate comprising (2R,3R)- and (2S,3S)-2,3-dihydro-3-hydroxyanthranilic acid zwitterion.
A cyclic ketone consisting of cyclohex-3-en-1-one substituted at position 5 by a carboxy group and position 6 by an amino group.
A 6-amino-5-oxocyclohex-2-ene-1-carboxylic acid in which both stereocentres have R-configuration.
A 6-amino-5-oxocyclohex-2-ene-1-carboxylic acid in which both stereocentres have S-configuration.
A 6-amino-5-oxocyclohex-2-ene-1-carboxylic acid in which stereocentre attached to the carboxylic acid group has R-configuration, while that attached to the amino group has S-configuration.
A 6-amino-5-oxocyclohex-2-ene-1-carboxylic acid in which stereocentre attached to the carboxylic acid group has S-configuration, while that attached to the amino group has R-configuration.
An amino acid zwitterion, obtained by transfer of a proton from the carboxylic acid group to the amino group of (1R,6R)-6-amino-5-oxocyclohex-2-ene-1-carboxylic acid.
An amino acid zwitterion, obtained by transfer of a proton from the carboxylic acid group to the amino group of 6-amino-5-oxocyclohex-2-ene-1-carboxylic acid zwitterion.
An amino acid zwitterion, obtained by transfer of a proton from the carboxylic acid group to the amino group of (1S,6S)-6-amino-5-oxocyclohex-2-ene-1-carboxylic acid.
An amino acid zwitterion, obtained by transfer of a proton from the carboxylic acid group to the amino group of (1R,6S)-6-amino-5-oxocyclohex-2-ene-1-carboxylic acid.
An amino acid zwitterion, obtained by transfer of a proton from the carboxylic acid group to the amino group of (1S,6R)-6-amino-5-oxocyclohex-2-ene-1-carboxylic acid.
A 6-ammonio-5-oxocyclohex-2-ene-1-carboxylate racemate comprising (1R,6R)- and (1S,6S)-6-ammonio-5-oxocyclohex-2-ene-1-carboxylate.
A racemate comprising (1R,6R)- and (1S,6S)-6-amino-5-oxocyclohex-2-ene-1-carboxylic acid.
A racemate comprising (1R,6S)- and (1S,6R)-6-amino-5-oxocyclohex-2-ene-1-carboxylic acid.
A 6-ammonio-5-oxocyclohex-2-ene-1-carboxylate racemate comprising (1R,6S)- and (1S,6R)-6-ammonio-5-oxocyclohex-2-ene-1-carboxylate.

A quaternary ammonium salt in which the quaternary nitrogen is substituted by a 2,3-dioleyloxypropyl group, a [2-(sperminecarboxamido)ethyl group, and two methyl groups, and in which the positive charged is balanced by a trifluoroacetate anion.
An organic phosphoramidate that is 5'-O-[amino(3-aminopropoxy)phosphoryl]adenosine in which the nitrogen of the phosphoramidite is acylated by a (2S)-2-amino-3-carboxypropanoyl group.
A fatty acid anion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group of an aza fatty acid.
The selenium ion with two positive charges.
Indoline substituted with hydroxy groups at C-5 and -6 and a carboxy group at C-2, and with S stereochemistry at C-2.
A 2',3'-cyclic nucleotide(1-) which is obtained from 2',3'-cyclic UMP by removal of a proton from the cyclic phosphate group.
A monocarboxylic acid anion obtained by removal of a proton from the carboxylic acid group of phenylacetylglycine. The major species of phenylacetylglycine at pH 7.3.
A  nucleoside 3'-phosphate(2-) which results from the removal of two protons from the phosphate group of 3'-CMP; major species at pH 7.3.
A glycosylglucose comprising beta-D-glucose having a D-galactosyl residue at the 4-position.
A 2',3'-cyclic nucleotide(1-) which is obtained from 2',3'-cyclic CMP by removal of a proton from the cyclic phosphate group.
